On Wed, 8 Feb 2006 claralw(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> I've run a 28 pict on a 1600 sp in a bus, and liked it.  In fact a couple years ago swapped to the 28 from a so pict, and got better gas milage, though the acceleration was different than with the 30.  A bit less pull at lower rpms.    Doesn't run hot... I have oil temp guage.
> I think they were designed for a 40hp, but I have had no issues with one on a 1600.  My first bus has one, and it got 31 mpg regularly.   For 3 years.

Small carburators are ususally great for mileage.  The only difference you
will see is in top end performance, since the small hole won't flow as
much air as a large hole.  As long as the carb is jetted right you won't
have any heating problems.

George Lyle
